#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/rerender-split-combined-hooks.md
M|rules|title: Split Combined Hook Computations
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids recomputing independent steps
M|rules|tags: rerender, useMemo, useEffect, dependencies, optimization
M|rules|When a hook contains multiple independent tasks with different dependencies, split them into separate hooks. A combined hook reruns all tasks when any dependency changes, even if some tasks don't use 
M|rules|**Incorrect (changing `sortOrder` recomputes filtering):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|const sortedProducts = useMemo(() => {
M|rules|const filtered = products.filter((p) => p.category === category)
M|rules|const sorted = filtered.toSorted((a, b) =>
M|rules|sortOrder === "asc" ? a.price - b.price : b.price - a.price
M|rules|)
M|rules|return sorted
M|rules|}, [products, category, sortOrder])
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (filtering only recomputes when products or category change):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|const filteredProducts = useMemo(
M|rules|() => products.filter((p) => p.category === category),
M|rules|[products, category]
M|rules|)
M|rules|const sortedProducts = useMemo(
M|rules|() =>
M|rules|filteredProducts.toSorted((a, b) =>
M|rules|sortOrder === "asc" ? a.price - b.price : b.price - a.price
M|rules|),
M|rules|[filteredProducts, sortOrder]
M|rules|)
M|rules|```
M|rules|This pattern also applies to `useEffect` when combining unrelated side effects:
M|rules|**Incorrect (both effects run when either dependency changes):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|anl.trackPageView(pathname)
M|rules|doc.title = `${pageTitle} | My App`
M|rules|}, [pathname, pageTitle])
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (effects run independently):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|anl.trackPageView(pathname)
M|rules|}, [pathname])
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|doc.title = `${pageTitle} | My App`
M|rules|}, [pageTitle])
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Note:** If your project has [React Compiler](https://react.dev/learn/react-compiler) enabled, it automatically optimizes dependency tracking and may handle some of these cases for you.